password="false" selected="false" bounds="[42,752][1038,2194]"><node index="0" text='Digital Arhat: Admin Action Stabilization (Auth-Path Hardening)&#10;​1. Files Modified&#10;​lib/services/auth_service.dart&#10;​lib/services/admin_action_service.dart&#10;​lib/dashboard/admin/admin_dashboard.dart&#10;​lib/dashboard/admin/admin_listing_detail_screen.dart&#10;​lib/auth/auth_wrapper.dart&#10;​firestore.rules&#10;​2. Exact Root Cause Found&#10;​"Auth-Session Disconnect." Jab Admin "Custom Login" (Phone/Password) karta tha, to Local Session active ho jata tha par FirebaseAuth.instance.currentUser aksar null rehta tha. Kyunki Firestore aur Callable Functions request.auth par rely karte hain, isliye saare Admin actions permission-denied par phans rahe thay.&#10;​3. Firebase request.auth Mismatch Blocker&#10;​YES. Yehi asli rukawat thi. UI ko lag raha tha Admin logged-in hai (Local UID ki wajah se), lekin Firebase Backend ko request.auth == null mil raha tha, jis se security rules ne saari writes block kar di thin.&#10;​4. Exact Failing Firestore Paths&#10;​listings/{listingId} (Update: listingStatus)&#10;​admin_action_logs/{logId} (Create: Audit logs)&#10;​revenue_ledger/{entryId} (Create: Promotion tracking)&#10;​notifications/{notifId} (Create: Admin-triggered alerts)&#10;​5. Exact Production Fix Applied&#10;​"Lazy-Auth Restoration Layer":&#10;Maine AdminActionService mein har action se pehle ek blocking check lagaya hai. Agar FirebaseAuth user missing hai, to app local credentials use karke Firebase Session restore karti hai theek action fire karne se pehle. Saath hi, [PROD_AUTH] diagnostics add kiye hain taake runtime par session status verify ho sakay.&#10;​6. firestore.rules Fixed or Not&#10;​YES. Rules mein admin_action_logs aur revenue_ledger ki definitions missing thin, jisay add kar diya gaya hai taake Admin ki legitimate writes block na hon.&#10;​7. Flutter Analyze Result (Allowed Files Only)&#10;​PASS. Specific files (auth_service, admin_action_service, etc.) m